features: ✅ START YOUR TRUCK REMOTELY - Use the most complete Plug N Play Remote Starter KIT to warm or cool your truck, by pressing lock 3 times on your existing remote. 😊
✅ COMPATIBILITY – This kit is compatible with RAM Pickup Trucks. 1500/2500/3500 2013 2014 2015 2016 2017 Key Start (Tip Start). Will not work with Push to Start trucks.
✅ PLUG ‘N PLAY T-HARNESS – The included Start-X T-Harness eliminates all wire splicing and tapping.✅ ✅ Windows PC is required to complete the programming process.
✅PROGRAMMING – Computer is required to complete the installation. Windows or Mac.

✅ RANGE – The distance you can remote start from is the same distance you can lock/unlock your truck. You may want to test your remote to see if it’s enough for your remote start needs. Plug N Play long range remotes are available at an additional discounted cost.

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Plug N Play Remote Start Kit YES! You can install a remote starter yourself. Please don’t pay exuberant dealer fees to have the dealer do what you can do yourself. The Start-X kit was designed with YOU in mind. You, the average car owner that can fix a thing or 2 yourself. The included T-harness greatly simplifies installation. Completely Plug N Play. ZERO WIRE TAPPING!

Using Your New System - 3X Lock The module will monitor the OEM remote for 3X Lock and will start your vehicle when you press lock 3 times. An aftermarket remote is not necessary, there are no extra key fobs to carry around.
Unique Start-X T-Harness The included T-harness is a unique Start-X T-Harness that can not be found anywhere else. The T-harness is neat and avoids the the usual "rats nest" of wires.
Complete Kit The kit contains everything you need for a successful installation, We even include a pry tool to pop the panels and zip ties to secure the module.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very quick install, and it WORKS!
reviews.reviewText: Total labor is to remove two screws, and then snap in two in line harnesses. The programming is tedius, so take your time and be patient. Involves using your desktop to flash the little computer that comes with it. You basically wire it in, do some steps with the key. Then you remove it (three little clip on harnesses) and bring it in to your desktop, and run a program you download. THEN, you go back out, reconnect it and do a few more steps (turn key, watch for blinking light, turen key back...), and DONE. Actually works. Money well spent.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars STEP BY STEP INSTRUCTIONS BELOW FOR 14’ RAM 1500! EASY!!
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. I can’t believe how easy this was to install and program! Maybe 30 minutes from start to finish with programming.You do jump around in the instructions a bit, but it’s incredibly easy, just follow the instructions. Downloading the firmware was easy. Sign up, check your junk mail for activation email, activate account. Download what the book says to download. Works for Mac and windows.STEP BY STEP (2014 RAM 1500),1. Install new obd T-harness.2. Remove dash panel.3. Install “main T-harness” ignition harness to ignition.4. Connect main t-harness to new obd harness via the canbus connector.5. While connecting black connector to module, hold reset button, hold until red light flashes on module.6. Connect blue and white connectors to module.7. Close driver door.8. Open driver door.9. Press unlock multiple times on factory key fob until module LED flashes green.10. Turn Key to ON position and wait for LED on module to turn solid red. (I accidentally started mine, but it worked.)11. Turn key off12. Remove key13. Insert key and start vehicle.14. Wait for LED on module to flash green and remove key.15. Disconnect blue and white plug from module FIRST!16. Disconnect black module plug LAST.17. Head inside to flash module on computer. Internet access needed to sign up and download Weblink Desktop Software.18. Click “Sign up” button in top right corner at weblinkupdater.com19. Sign up.20. Check JUNK mail for activation email.21. Resend activation link if email doesn’t show up within a minute.22. Download weblink desktop software.23. Plug in module with supplied USB adapter.24. Open Weblink software.25. Click Weblink RS.26. Click “Start Extended Programming”.27. Click “Continue Extended Programming”.28. Once complete, unhook module and head back out to vehicle.29. Reconnect module, all three plugs. White, blue, black. (If colors haven’t changed)30. Turn key to ON position.31. LED should turn solid GREEN for 2 seconds. According to the book, of it doesn’t turn green, try proceeding anyway. (It came on for me).32. Turn key to OFF position.33. Start the vehicle.34. Turn off the vehicle and remove key.35. Get out and close door.36. Press lock button on key fob 3 times.37. Vehicle starts!!!!!!38. Unlock vehicle39. Open door, get in, close door. (Important for anti-theft)39. Insert Key and turn to run position.40. Press brake.41. Select Drive or Reverse.42. Go for a test drive!36-41 have to happen in that order every time you start the truck or the truck will go into anti-theft and shut off. I saw a lot of complaints about this, but I love it because it protects you as the owner!!Very simple! Pretty impressed with myself and you will be too! 😉

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 12, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Somewhat confusing, easy installation though.
reviews.reviewText: Installed on a 2017 Ram 1500 CC with Tip Key. I have never installed a remote start kit.. I know the basics of vehicles, so this wasn’t incredibly hard. If you know the basics, I would save the money and do it yourself. Shoot, even if you don’t, save the money and DIY- it’s not hard at all.1st off, I had to buy a used dell laptop from OfferUp since it’s not supported for Mac laptops, which kind of sucked. However, that was probably way cheaper than getting it professionally installed.2nd, the instructions kind of sucked.. I had to re-read the instructions a few times since they were vague. Once understood, the install was a breeze. I had no hiccups during install. In fact, this is the easiest and smoothest aftermarket install I’ve ever done on any vehicle. Make sure you use internet explorer or else it’ll say it’s not compatible. I’d recommend this product to anybody wanting to do a DIY install. It’ll take a little bit to get used to starting it, but I’m so excited. Being in Arizona, it’ll be nice to have remote start during 115+ summers and below 32 winter mornings. I never had to reach out to customer service or re flash the device. Just make sure you thoroughly follow the directions. My biggest complaint and improvement to the developer would be better instructions and to have an installation video guide to go along with.Update: I have since downgraded to a 1 star. After 3 months, suddenly my ECU did not recognize both of my key fobs. This messed with my computer system and left me stranded several times. Once I removed the product, my truck started working fine. It also caused computer glitches to have my truck driving at 5500 RPM at 45mph. Not sure what was going with this product.
